
---


@startuml

' Entities
class University {
}

class Department {
}

class ResearchGroup {
    - name: String
    - department: Department
}

class Researcher {
    - name: String
    - researchGroup: ResearchGroup
}

class Project {
    - title: String
}

class WorkPackage {
    - title: String
    - project: Project
    - leader: ResearchGroup
}

class WPAssignment {
    - researcher: Researcher
    - workPackage: WorkPackage
    - startDate: Date
    - endDate: Date (optional)
}

' Associations

University "1" -- "many" Department
Department "1" -- "many" ResearchGroup
ResearchGroup "1" -- "many" Researcher
Researcher "1" -- "many" WPAssignment
WorkPackage "1" -- "many" WPAssignment
Project "1" -- "many" WorkPackage
WorkPackage "1" -- "1" ResearchGroup : isLedBy

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Concepts:

- **University → Department**: A university has multiple departments.
- **Department → ResearchGroup**: Each department hosts multiple research groups.
- **ResearchGroup → Researcher**: Researchers belong to exactly one research group.
- **Project → WorkPackage**: Projects are composed of multiple work packages.
- **WorkPackage → ResearchGroup**: Every work package is led by one research group.
- **Researcher ↔ WPAssignment ↔ WorkPackage**: Researchers can be assigned to any work package, regardless of leadership group.
- **WPAssignment**: This class tracks when a researcher was assigned to a work package, with optional end date to reflect termination or change due to group reassignment.

